aw as a more diffuse attention to the religiousness of contemporary life. The group wondered what reading these textures of religion in these volumes might say about our times, about writing, and about themselves. The Abyss or Life is Simple is the culmination of this collective endeavor—a collection of interlocking essays on ritual, beauty, and the end of the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  areligion, world literature, faith, belief, ritual, fiction, philosophy, aesthetics, life of a writer, disillusionment, secularism, art, intertextuality, sacred, holy, meaning, purpose, fulfillment, human nature, divine, norway, scandinavia, struggle, suffering, pain, comfort, beauty, knausgaard, nonfiction, criticism, novel, community.1 aBender, Courtney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiles, Jeremy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBiles, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarlson, Liane, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCarlson, Liane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper Harriss, M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDubler, Joshua, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFallers Sullivan, Winnifred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarvey, Hannah C., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGarvey, Hannah C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarriss, M. Cooper, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSullivan, Winnifred Fallers, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aThorstensen, Erik, eauthor.4aut4http://id.l